properties.areaDesc: Ferris/Seminoe/Shirley Mountains; Shirley Basin; Central Laramie County; East Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 2:11AM MST until February 1 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS WILL CONTINUE THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT FOR
WIND PRONE AREAS...

* WHAT...West to southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65
mph.

* WHERE...Ferris/Seminoe/Shirley Mountains, Shirley Basin, East
Platte County and Central Laramie County Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 8 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous,
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles including
camping and tractor trailers. Blowing snow will result in low
visibility and slick roads.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 8 PM MST THIS EVENING
